Task: Rename the 'formatData' function to 'prettyFormat' across all files, including both the function definition and all its usages.

Expected changes:
1. In utils/format.js: Rename function and update exports
2. In api/response.js: Update the imported function name
3. In views/display.js: Update the function usage
4. In tests/format.test.js: Update test descriptions and function calls

Solution steps:
1. :args **/*.js to recursively select all JavaScript files
2. :argdo %s/\<formatData\>/prettyFormat/g to rename function (word boundaries prevent partial matches)
3. :argdo update to save changes

Alternative approaches:
- Use :grep "formatData" **/*.js then :cdo s/formatData/prettyFormat/g
- Use :vimgrep /formatData/ **/*.js then :cfdo %s/formatData/prettyFormat/g 